# WordPress Studio & MCP Setup

## Architecture

- **Next.js frontend** (this repo): Fetches content via WordPress REST API
- **WordPress backend**: CMS for posts and events (run in WordPress Studio locally)

## WordPress Studio

- Import backups: `.tar.gz`, `.zip`, or `.wpress`
- Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORDPRESS_URL` in `.env` to the Studio site URL (e.g. `http://brookkatz.local`)
- WordPress must expose: `posts`, custom `events` post type, ACF fields (`event_date`, `event_time`, `event_location`)

## MCP Browser Preview

1. Run `npm run dev` before using browser MCP tools
2. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000` to preview the Next.js frontend
3. To inspect the CMS, navigate to the WordPress Studio URL (e.g. `http://brookkatz.local/wp-admin`)
